==Description== <!--T:3-->

<!--T:4-->
The [[Image:Curves_SegmentSurface.svg|24px]] [[Curves_SegmentSurface|Curves SegmentSurface]] allows to segment a surface on isocurves. This tool is part of the [[External_workbenches|external workbench]] called [[Curves_Workbench|Curves]].

==Usage== <!--T:5-->

<!--T:6-->
# Switch to the [[Image:Curves_workbench_icon.svg|24px]] [[Curves_Workbench|Curves]] workbench (install from [[Image:Std_AddonMgr.svg|24px]] [[Std_AddonMgr|Addon Manager]] is necessary, if not previously installed)
# To invoke the command, do one of the following:
#* Press the [[Image:Curves_SegmentSurface.svg|24px]] button in the Curves toolbar.
#* Use the {{MenuCommand|Surfaces → Segment surface}} entry in the dropdown menu.


